{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015GyUSCrLUZxLuGdDuVu78k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The resource statefulset.yaml shows:\n1. ES should use version 8.11.1 with the repository-s3 plugin installed\n2. The secure-settings are mounted as a volume from the `es-secure-settings` secret\n3. The initContainer installs the repository-s3 plugin\n\nBut the current cluster is running ES 7.17.9 without the plugin or secure settings volume. The statefulset.yaml in resources defines the correct target state.\n\nThe current state:\n- es-cluster StatefulSet: ES 7.17.9, no init containers, no secure-settings mount\n- MinIO isn't deployed yet, and neither are the minio-root or es-secure-settings secrets\n\nSo I need to deploy MinIO first by applying the minio-secret, minio deployment, and updating services, then create the minio-init job to set up the bucket, create the es-secure-settings secret, and finally upgrade the ES StatefulSet to 8.11.1 with the plugin installer and secure-settings volume mounted.\n\nFor the S3 repository credentials, I should use the Elasticsearch keystore rather than putting them in elasticsearch.yml or environment variables. The resources were designed to work together, so I'll apply the MinIO components first and wait for them to be ready before configuring the ES side. The current state has ES 7.17.9 without the plugin and no MinIO, so I need to deploy MinIO first, create the secure settings secret, then update the ES StatefulSet to include the repository-s3 plugin via an init container and mount the secure-settings volume. After that I can configure the keystore, register the snapshot repository, and create a snapshot. Let me check what the oracle validates to make sure I'm on the right track.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1462,"cac