{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PRhJwisoJK2MaeQSkUTBcE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oracle passes. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**What was configured:**\n\n1. **Deployed MinIO** — applied `minio-root` secret, MinIO deployment, and MinIO service into the `elasticsearch` namespace (these were missing because the precondition probe skipped the apply step).\n\n2. **Created `es-secure-settings` secret** — contains `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (credentials never touch `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars).\n\n3. **Updated the ES ConfigMap** — added S3 endpoint config (`s3.client.default.endpoint`, `protocol`, `path_style_access`) to `elasticsearch.yml` (endpoint settings only, no credentials).\n\n4. **Patched the StatefulSet** — added an initContainer that installs `repository-s3` plugin into a shared emptyDir on pod start, plus the secure-settings volume mount.\n\n5. **Scaled to 3 nodes** — deleted es-cluster-0 to pick up the new spec (plugin initContainer), then scaled to 3 replicas.\n\n6. **Populated keystore on all 3 nodes** — added `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` via `elasticsearch-keystore add -x`, then called `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings`.\n\n7. **Created the `es-backups` bucket** — via the `minio-init` job using the MinIO CLI.\n\n8. **Registered `minio-repo`** snapshot repository (type `s3`, bucket `es-backups`).\n\n9. **Created snapshot `snap-001`** — completed with `state: SUCCESS` across all 6 shards."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":178,"cache_read_input_tokens":59558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":178},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5af14cc